               </location>
               <listBibl type="secondary">
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:BerryEtAl2005EnAeGondar"/></bibl>
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Wubneh2003EnAeAngarab"/></bibl>
               </listBibl>
               <note>
                  <ab type="description">There are two rivers known by the name Āngarab. This record
                     refers to the so called Small Āngarab (cfr. <placeName ref="LOC6536Angara"
                        >Great Āngarab</placeName>) which rises a few miles north of <placeName
                        ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> and flows southwards to join the
                        <placeName ref="LOC4402Magac">Megeč̣</placeName> river, which in turn
                     empties into the lake <placeName ref="LOC5889Tana">Ṭānā</placeName>. The Small
                     Āngarab and the <placeName ref="LOC5148Qaha">Qaha</placeName> river skirt the
                     western and eastern sides of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>
                     respectively. They are the main sources of water of the city and they join
                     south of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> near <placeName
                        ref="LOC2999EslamB">Ǝslam Bet</placeName>, before joining the <placeName
                        ref="LOC4402Magac">Megeč̣</placeName> river.</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
